\begin{definition}\label{def:R-CC}
For positive integers $q$ and $r$, let $R \subseteq [q]^r$ be a relation of arity $r$ over $[q]$.
The input of the $R$-\CC problem consists of a graph $G=(V,E)$ and a collection $\calF \subseteq V^r$ of $r$-tuples of vertices.
The goal is to decide whether there exists a proper coloring $c:V \to [q]$ of $G$, such that for every $r$-tuple $(x_1, \ldots, x_r) \in \calF$, it holds that $(c(x_1), \ldots, c(x_r)) \in R$. The number of constraints in the instance $(G,\calF)$ is $|E|+|\calF|$.
\end{definition}

