\begin{definition}\label{def:OR definable}
Let $q$, $r$, and $k$ be positive integers, and let $R \subseteq [q]^r$ be a relation of arity $r$ over $[q]$.
We say that {\em an \OR relation of arity $k$ is definable from $R$} if there exist sets $D_1, \ldots, D_r \subseteq [q]$, exactly $k$ of which are of size $2$ and the others of size $1$, such that all $2^k$ tuples in the product $D_1 \times \cdots \times D_r$ except one belong to $R$, equivalently, $| (D_1 \times \cdots \times D_r) \cap R| = 2^k-1$.
\end{definition}

